<p class="article-lead">Perfume is often dangerous goods in transport because alcohol-based formulas can be flammable. Classification is based on the actual product and transport rules, not on whether the retail package appears harmless.</p><p>Alcoholic perfumery products are commonly associated with UN 1266 and Class 3, but the applicable packing group, limited-quantity provisions and carrier acceptance require product data and route review. Formula, flash point, inner bottle size, total quantity and mode all matter.</p><p>Use compliant inner and outer packaging, marks, labels and documentation prepared by competent parties. Courier acceptance for a few samples does not prove that the same route can carry a commercial shipment.</p><p class="article-source-note"><a href="https://unece.org/transport/dangerous-goods/un-model-regulations-rev-23" target="_blank" rel="noopener">UNECE Model Regulations</a></p>
